src_text: Pegelo ka ga Pusoselegae
trg_text: Report on Local Government

src_text: Kabinete e sekasekile maemo a pusoselegae morago ga go bona dipegelo go tswa go Lefapha la Pusotshwaraganelo le Merero ya Setso (CoGTA), Lefapha la Matlotlo a Set haba le Morunikakaretso wa Aforika Borw
trg_text: Cabinet discussed the state of local government informed by the reports from the Department of Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs (CoGTA), National Treasury and Auditor-General South Afric

src_text: Kabinete e etse tlhoko maemo a a sa namatsheng a dingwe tsa bommasepala mme mo makgetlong a mangwe, puso ya boset haba e tla tshwanela ke go tsereganya go tokafatsa thebolo ya ditirelo le bokgoni jwa bommasepala ba ba rileng go ya ka metheo ya Karolo 139(7) ya Molaotheo wa Rephaboliki ya Aforika Borwa wa 1996.
trg_text: Cabinet noted the dire state of some municipalities and that in some instances, national government will have to intervene decisively to improve service delivery and the capacity of specific municipalities in line with the provisions of Section 139(7) of the Constitution of the Republic of South Africa of 1993.

src_text: Mo godimo ga moo, puso ya boset haba e eteletswe pele ke CoGTA, Lefapha la Matlotlo a Set haba le mafapha a thebolo ya ditirelo a tla matlafatsa tshegetso ya bona go bommasepala go ya ka Mmotlele wa Tlhabololo o o ikaegileng ka Sedika (DDM) le maikarabelo a tsona jaaka go tlhalositswe mo Karolo 154 ya Molaotheo
trg_text: In addition, national government led by CoGTA, National Treasury and service-delivery departments will strengthen their support to municipalities in line with the District-based Development Model (DDM) and their responsibilities as provided for in Section 154 of the Constitution

src_text: Mo botshelong jwa gagwe, Ngaka Kaunda o dirile ka natla a direla tswelopele ya ikonomi, loago le sepolotiki mo Aforika, mme e ne e le moganka wa Kgaratlhelo ya Aforika e e gololosegileng go tswa go taolo ya bokoloniale le tlhaolel O eteletse pele botho ba Seaforika, mme o tla gopolwa ka boeteledipele jo bo tswileng diatla jwa gagwe mo go tlhamiweng ga Mokgatlho wa Tshwaragano ya Aforika(o ga jaana o bidiwang Mokgatlhotshwaraganelo wa Aforika).
trg_text: Throughout his life, Dr Kaunda worked tirelessly for economic, social and political progress in Africa, and was a giant of the Struggle for an Africa free from colonial and apartheid rul He championed African humanism, and will be fondly remembered for his outstanding leadership in the formation of the Non-Aligned Movement and the then Organisation of African Unity (now called African Union).

src_text: Kabinete e atlenegisitse lenaneo le le eteletsweng pele ke Lefapha la Metshameko, Botaki le Setso go tlotla botshelo le seabe sa Ngaka Kaunda go kgololosego ya naga ya gagwe le kontinente, bogolosegolo kgaolo ya Borweng ba Aforik Moporesidente Ramaphosa o tla tsenela tirelo ya phitlho e e tla tshwarwang kwa Lusaka ka Labotlhano, 2 Phukwi 2021.
trg_text: Cabinet endorsed a programme led by the Department of Sport, Arts and Culture to pay tribute to the life and contribution of Dr Kaunda to the liberation of his own country and the continent, particularly the Southern African regio President Ramaphosa will attend the funeral to be held in Lusaka on Friday, 2 July 2021.
